cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating a high-resolution surface reconstruction from a single image. It may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves generating 3D reconstructions. The use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the efficient representation of the surface reconstruction suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks and learning (cs.NE) sub-category.
